  "title": "Key Account Manager (Local / East / Freight Forwarding)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Build and manage strong, lasting relationships with high-value global and regional accounts.</li>\n  <li>Develop long-term account strategies to retain clients and expand business opportunities.</li>\n  <li>Understand client needs, resolve issues quickly, and provide tailored solutions.</li>\n  <li>Strengthen customer relationships to create mutually beneficial partnerships.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate closely with internal teams to deliver excellent service and ensure client requirements are met.</li>\n  <li>Identify and pursue new business opportunities within existing accounts.</li>\n  <li>Prepare regular account reports and manage account receivables efficiently.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Business, Sales, Logistics, or related fields.</li>\n  <li>3–5 years of experience in logistics or freight forwarding with a focus on sales and business development.</li>\n  <li>Experience handling key or conglomerate accounts, preferably in <strong>Healthcare, Semiconductor, or Electronics</strong> sectors.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication, negotiation, and presentation skills.</li>\n  <li>Strategic thinker with strong analytical, problem-solving, and relationship-building abilities.</li>\n  <li>Proactive, results-oriented, and comfortable working independently or in a team.</li>\n  <li>Candidates with leadership experience may be considered for a <strong>Senior Key Account Manager</strong> position.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No. 20C0270</p>",
